company that invests in shopping malls and offices, is in talks
with Barclays Bank Plc to review loan agreements, the Sunday
Telegraph reported, without citing where it got the information.  The London-based company wants a standstill agreement for
the Agora Max fund, which owns two shopping centers in northwest
